# Documentation Source of Truth

- Treat `docs/ARCHITECTURE/GRAPHICS_PIPELINE.md` as canonical for graphics behavior and constraints.
- If changing graphics behavior, update relevant docs under `docs/ARCHITECTURE/`, `docs/ROADMAP/`, and `docs/EXECUTION/` in the same task.
- If implementation conflicts with durable assumptions, add or update an ADR under `docs/ADR/`.
- Do not leave accepted behavior changes undocumented.
- For any build/enhancement/bugfix request, run `.cursor/skills/docs-implementation-gate/SKILL.md` as the default docs workflow.
- When docs conflict or authority is unclear, run `.cursor/skills/docs-source-truth-resolver/SKILL.md` before implementation.
- After behavior/scope/assumption changes, run `.cursor/skills/docs-change-policy-enforcer/SKILL.md` before finalizing.
- If a durable decision or locked assumption changes, run `.cursor/skills/docs-adr-decision-recorder/SKILL.md`.
- If a new documentation artifact is needed, run `.cursor/skills/docs-template-author/SKILL.md`.
